00:00:00.199 --> 00:00:05.640
&gt;&gt;presenter: So, David, for many years, was
a senior editor for Internet technology at

00:00:05.640 --> 00:00:11.690
Fortune Magazine and he did a number of cover
stories on Internet giants and tech giants,

00:00:11.690 --> 00:00:20.460
like Microsoft and IBM and Intel. And David's
latest project is an inside look, with the

00:00:20.460 --> 00:00:26.320
support of Facebook's executives, at Facebook
and it's something that I'm sure you're all

00:00:26.320 --> 00:00:27.320
familiar with.

00:00:27.320 --> 00:00:33.440
Facebook, as we know, started in Mark Zuckerberg's
dorm room and in the last six years has really

00:00:33.440 --> 00:00:42.230
skyrocketed to a site that has over five hundred
million members worldwide. So, David has written

00:00:42.230 --> 00:00:47.760
a book that gives us an inside look at not
only Facebook and the evolution of that company,

00:00:47.760 --> 00:00:54.380
but how the concept of connecting people is
really changing the world. So, without further

00:00:54.380 --> 00:00:58.489
ado, please welcome David Kirkpatrick. Thank
you.

